to, to participate in groups online and learn

00:31:32.649 --> 00:31:33.820
about this middle information.

00:31:33.820 --> 00:31:35.090
[audience chatter]

00:31:35.090 --> 00:31:39.259
The fifth change is that venues and availability
of information have changed. It used to be

00:31:39.259 --> 00:31:43.030
that we had appointments with media. We watched
certain TV shows at certain times that they

00:31:43.030 --> 00:31:48.330
were on; we watched on the different platforms
that they were made available on that, that,

00:31:48.330 --> 00:31:52.429
we did it on a schedule that they gave us.
Well now, in the era of mobile connectivity

00:31:52.429 --> 00:31:57.000
devices that give us media anytime and anywhere,
we are in charge of the playlist.

00:31:57.000 --> 00:32:03.490
We are watching TV on something other than
a traditional TV. We're reading newspapers

00:32:03.490 --> 00:32:09.639
on something other than traditional newspapers
and it's rebalanced the relationship the people

00:32:09.639 --> 00:32:14.279
who used to be the producers and articulators
of the scheduling of the information and the

00:32:14.279 --> 00:32:18.559
consumers, who now have much more control,
not only of, of when they're going to encounter

00:32:18.559 --> 00:32:23.549
media, but their capacity to, to contribute
to media.

00:32:23.549 --> 00:32:27.559
The sixth change is the vibrance of information
has changed, too. The immersive qualities

00:32:27.559 --> 00:32:32.269
of information in this age has gotten a lot
better as computing power, bandwidth has grown,

00:32:32.269 --> 00:32:38.090
th-,even the pixels we can display have become
more tightly packed and more colorful. There

00:32:38.090 --> 00:32:43.640
are now more engaging worlds, particularly
in the gaming environment, but also in all

00:32:43.640 --> 00:32:49.040
kinds of, of, in virtual spaces that are pretty
compelling, and pretty interesting and pretty

00:32:49.040 --> 00:32:54.669
connected to what, what interest's people.
I would argue that, y-, that, that, that this

00:32:54.669 --> 00:32:58.950
company in particular is at the forefront
of true trends that we are going to be measuring

00:32:58.950 --> 00:33:03.950
a lot in the coming, in the coming years just
because they speak to this issue of the, of

00:33:03.950 --> 00:33:08.539
the vibrance of information--augmented reality.
I mean, we're just packing more stuff as we

00:33:08.539 --> 00:33:13.309
merge the virtual and real worlds with data
on top of, of real artifacts and real landscapes

00:33:13.309 --> 00:33:14.309
and things.

00:33:14.309 --> 00:33:18.330
People are en-, engaging most spaces now in
different ways in the mobile environment and

00:33:18.330 --> 00:33:23.929
we'll do so even more still as more information
gets packed in, more knowledge gets embedded

00:33:23.929 --> 00:33:28.200
in artifacts and as the apps get better. It's
just, it's just that simple and of course,

00:33:28.200 --> 00:33:32.990
Mirror Worlds, you guys have given us the
iconic example of that in, in Google Earth.

00:33:32.990 --> 00:33:37.499
It just, these are just powerful tools now
where stuff that we know and we experience

00:33:37.499 --> 00:33:43.679
can be embedded into representations of the
real world. I, that makes people more capable

00:33:43.679 --> 00:33:47.600
of being actors in that real world in the
sense of, of network individualism.

00:33:47.600 --> 00:33:53.320
The seventh change is the balance of information
has gotten better. We find more stuff that

00:33:53.320 --> 00:33:57.080
is relevant to us than ever before, thanks
in large part because search engines are doing

00:33:57.080 --> 00:34:03.179
such a wonderful job at that. The Semantic
Web mi-, might be even better at, at, at giving

00:34:03.179 --> 00:34:07.240
us information like that, but even in simple
forms now about half of Internet users, in

00:34:07.240 --> 00:34:12.060
one way, shape, or form, customize information
flows into them. They, they set up RSS feeds,

00:34:12.060 --> 00:34:16.820
they, they customize a web page, they build,
they belong to listservs or other kinds of

00:34:16.820 --> 00:34:23.150
groups that act as sentries and, and information
sources for them on the particular things

00:34:23.150 --> 00:34:24.390
that they care about.

00:34:24.390 --> 00:34:25.530
[audience chatter]

00:34:25.530 --> 00:34:28.240
The final change is in voting and ventilation
about in-, information is, well, actually

00:34:28.240 --> 00:34:29.350
let me take your question now. Yeah.

